-- German-Swiss Tax Accord May Finance Research, Handelsblatt Say
-- B y   B r i a n   P a r k i n
-- 2012-03-07T07:17:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-07/german-swiss-tax-accord-may-finance-research-handelsblatt-say.html
Germany  may use revenue generated by
a tax accord with  Switzerland  to finance technology research,
 Handelsblatt  reported.  As much as 4 billion euros ($5.3 billion) may be garnered
by the accord, according to estimates of the  Finance Ministry  in
Berlin, the newspaper said, citing Free Democrat lawmaker
Christian Lindner.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brian Parkin in Berlin at 
 bparkin@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Hertling at 
 jhertling@bloomberg.net  